{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"24e1384a-71f4-44ad-8721-501d21e93d7e","content":"\n\nHere are the most common options depending on your stack:\n\n**ASP.NET Core (`dotnet new`)**\n- `webapi` — minimal API or controller-based\n- Auth options: `--auth Individual` (Identity/JWT), `--auth IndividualB2C` (Azure AD B2C), `--auth SingleOrg` (Azure AD), `--auth Windows`\n\n**Node.js / Express**\n- Use `express-generator` or start from scratch\n- Auth: Passport.js (JWT, OAuth2, local), Auth0 SDK, Firebase Auth\n\n**Python / FastAPI**\n- `fastapi` with `python-jose` for JWT, or `authlib` for OAuth2\n\n**Java / Spring Boot**\n- `spring-boot-starter-web` + `spring-boot-starter-security`\n- Auth: JWT, OAuth2/OIDC via Spring Security\n\nFor a quick start with .NET:\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual -n MyApi\n```\n\nWould you like me to scaffold a project with a specific stack and auth type?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"399df901-f182-498b-83c1-31a63055023a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common web frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the most popular options.","outputTokens":315},"id":"91fa2838-6218-4c2b-b25f-402a51fc04fd","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:44:06.852Z","parentId":"7c62b8e5-bfd7-4b51-8171-bc80ad8045bd"}
